cie1000MstpMib.name: cie1000MstpMib

revisions.description: Added msti config table with msti value as the iteration key
Added range information for bridge parameters

cie1000MstpMib.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-snmp@cisco.com
cie1000MstpMib.description: This is a private version of the 802.1Q-2005 MSTP MIB

CIE1000MSTPForceVersion.name: CIE1000MSTPForceVersion
CIE1000MSTPForceVersion.description: This enumeration control the STP protocol variant to run.

CIE1000MstpPoint2Point.name: CIE1000MstpPoint2Point
CIE1000MstpPoint2Point.description: This enumeration describe the values of adminPointToPointMAC and operPointToPointMAC parameters. (Full duplex port administrative and operational status.) See 6.4.3 of IEEE Std 802.1D.

CIE1000MstpPortState.name: CIE1000MstpPortState
CIE1000MstpPortState.description: This enumeration describe the forwarding state of an interface.

cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBridgeHello.name: cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBridgeHelloTime
cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBridgeHello.description: Bridge Hello Time, 13.25.7 of IEEE-802.1Q-2005. Fixed value of two seconds by the standard, but this implementation allow a compatibility range from 1 to 2 seconds, in stipulated in 802.1Q-2005

cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsForceVersio.name: cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsForceVersion
cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsForceVersio.description: value of the Force Protocol Version parameter - 13.6.2 of IEEE-802.1Q-2005

cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBpduFilteri.name: cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBpduFiltering
cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBpduFilteri.description: BPDU filtering for edge ports. Control whether a port explicitly configured as Edge will transmit and receive BPDUs

cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBpduGuard.name: cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBpduGuard
cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsBpduGuard.description: BPDU guard for edge ports. Control whether a port explicitly configured as Edge will disable itself upon reception of a BPDU. The port will enter the error-disabled state, and will be removed from the active topology.

cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsErrorRecove.name: cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsErrorRecoveryDelay
cie1000MstpConfigBridgeParamsErrorRecove.description: The number of seconds until a STP inconsistent port is recovered. Valid values are zero (recovery disabled) or between 30 and 86400 (24 hours)

cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamTable.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamTable
cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamTable.description: This is a table of the bridge instance (MSTIs) parameters

cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamEntry.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamEntry
cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamEntry.description: Each MSTI has a set of parameters

cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamInstance.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamInstance
cie1000MstpConfigMstiParamInstance.description: Bridge instance number. The CIST = 0, MSTI1 = 1, etc

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigTable.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigTable
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigTable.description: This is the 802.1Q - 8.9 MST Configuration table For the purposes of calculating the Configuration Digest, the MST Configuration Table is considered to contain 4096 consecutive single octet elements, where each element of the table (with the exception of the first and last) contains an MSTID value.

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigEntry.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigEntry
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigEntry.description: The first element of the table contains the value 0, the second element the MSTID value corresponding to VID 1, the third element the MSTID value corresponding to VID 2, and so on, with the next to last element of the table containing the MSTID value corresponding to VID 4094, and the last element containing the value 0.

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigMstid.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigMstid
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigMstid.description: The MSTID value associated with the vlan id

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapTab.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapTable
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapTab.description: This is the 802.1Q - 8.9 MST Configuration table For the purposes of calculating the Configuration Digest, the MST Configuration Table is considered to contain 8 consecutive single octet elements, where each element of the table contains an vlan bitmap (vlans that have the MSTI value specified are set to one).

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapEnt.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapEntry
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapEnt.description: The first element of the table contains vlan bitmap corresponding to MSTI 0, the second element contains vlan bitmap corresponding to MSTI 1 until the 7th element. MSTI range is 0-7.

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAcc.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAccessVlans0To1K
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAcc.description: First quarter of bit-array indicating the enabled access VLANs.

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAcc.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAccessVlans1KTo2K
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAcc.description: Second quarter of bit-array indicating the enabled access VLANs.

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAcc.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAccessVlans2KTo3K
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAcc.description: Third quarter of bit-array indicating the enabled access VLANs.

cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAcc.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAccessVlans3KTo4K
cie1000MstpConfigMstiConfigVlanBitmapAcc.description: Last quarter of bit-array indicating the enabled access VLANs.

cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamTable.name: cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamTable
cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamTable.description: This is a table of the CIST physical interface parameters

cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamEntry.name: cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamEntry
cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamEntry.description: Each CIST physical interface has a set of parameters

cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamEnabl.name: cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamEnable
cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamEnabl.description: Control whether port is controlled by xSTP. If disabled, the port forwarding state follow the MAC state

cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamBpduG.name: cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamBpduGuard
cie1000MstpConfigCistInterfaceParamBpduG.description: If enabled, causes the port to disable itself upon receiving valid BPDU's. Contrary to the similar bridge setting, the port Edge status does not effect this setting. A port entering error-disabled state due to this setting is subject to the bridge ErrorRecoveryDelay setting as well

cie1000MstpConfigAggrParamsEnable.name: cie1000MstpConfigAggrParamsEnable
cie1000MstpConfigAggrParamsEnable.description: Control whether port is controlled by xSTP. If disabled, the port forwarding state follow the MAC state

cie1000MstpConfigAggrParamsBpduGuard.name: cie1000MstpConfigAggrParamsBpduGuard
cie1000MstpConfigAggrParamsBpduGuard.description: If enabled, causes the port to disable itself upon receiving valid BPDU's. Contrary to the similar bridge setting, the port Edge status does not effect this setting. A port entering error-disabled state due to this setting is subject to the bridge ErrorRecoveryDelay setting as well

cie1000MstpConfigMstiInterfaceParamInsta.description: Bridge instance number. The CIST = 0, MSTI1 = 1, etc

cie1000MstpConfigMstiInterfaceParamAdmin.name: cie1000MstpConfigMstiInterfaceParamAdminPortPriority
cie1000MstpConfigMstiInterfaceParamAdmin.description: priority field for the Port Identifier - 13.24.12 of 802.1Q-2005

cie1000MstpConfigMstiAggrParamInstance.description: Bridge instance number. The CIST = 0, MSTI1 = 1, etc

cie1000MstpConfigMstiAggrParamAdminPortP.description: priority field for the Port Identifier - 13.24.12 of 802.1Q-2005
